SIMPLE: unlaw
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unlaw
<hw>Un*law"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st <ets>un-</ets>
+ <ets>law</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To deprive of the authority or
character of law.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To put beyond protection of law; to outlaw.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Scots Law)</fld> <def>To impose a fine upon; to
fine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1578 -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unlaw</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unlaw
<hw>Un*law"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>un-</ets>
+ <ets>law</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Scots Law)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Any
transgression or offense against the law.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A fine
imposed as a penalty for violation of the law.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unlawed</ent>⟦br⟧
